ORGANIZER;CN=rsvp@figma.com:mailto:rsvp@figma.com
UID:226a928367e0f9296bb0bae3193bb1b38a218e2d@events.figma.com/des-systems-f
 ig-make
ATTENDEE;CUTYPE=INDIVIDUAL;ROLE=REQ-PARTICIPANT;PARTSTAT=ACCEPTED;CN=Sean W
 inslow;X-NUM-GUESTS=0:mailto:swinslow@theblock.co
URL:http://events.figma.com/des-systems-fig-make/virtual?guest-access-hash=
 NDU5MzAxODEyfDgzNzMwMjI4N3wxNzY0Nzk3MTAyOzFhYWEwMDg3NjY2MjY4OWMzNTdmZTU4NGY
 2MDg3YmEyM2UxODJhNjA0ZjdiNTU5NGIxZjQ0NjkxYzM5ZjJmODk%3D
CREATED:20251203T212515Z
DESCRIPTION:Here is your unique link - http://events.figma.com/des-systems-
 fig-make/virtual?guest-access-hash=NDU5MzAxODEyfDgzNzMwMjI4N3wxNzY0Nzk3MTAy
 OzFhYWEwMDg3NjY2MjY4OWMzNTdmZTU4NGY2MDg3YmEyM2UxODJhNjA0ZjdiNTU5NGIxZjQ0Njk
 xYzM5ZjJmODk%3D\n\nFor the best experience\, join this meeting on your desk
 top\n\nFigma Make enables builders of all kinds to generate high-quality pr
 ototypes quickly. But as we know\, functionality and speed are just one pie
 ce of the prototyping story. What’s just as important is how well those pro
 totypes align with your existing applications. <br><br><br />With Figma Mak
 e\, we’re striving to help your team create prototypes that not only look a
 nd feel like your designs\, but that actually utilize your design systems u
 nder the hood. <br><br>In this livestream\, Alex Mullans\, Product Manager 
 at Figma\, and Brandon Guo\, Software Engineer at Figma\, will discuss how 
 we are evolving Figma Make so that your team can:<br><br><br />• Leverage b
 oth public and private npm packages within Figma Make’s architecture.<br />
 • Improve Make’s ability to understand and utilize your design system compo
 nents through guidelines.<br />• Templatize core product surface areas in M
 ake to give builders on your team a consistent starting point.<br><br>Join 
 us for a presentation\, demo\, and live Q&A. We look forward to seeing you 
 there! \n
LAST-MODIFIED:20251203T212515Z
LOCATION:Virtual
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Design Systems in Figma Make
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
